The paper deals with modeling and analyzing the behavior of agents with present bias, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of graph-theoretic planning in the model suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses worst-case bounds and new phenomena, which are concepts that are often studied in the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and economics and computation (cs.EC).
